Package: modulr
Type: Package
Title: modulr -- Module Pattern Implementation for R
Version: 1.0
Date: 2015-01-16
Author: Alain Clément-Pavon <alain.clement-pavon@unil.ch>
Maintainer: Alain Clément-Pavon <alain.clement-pavon@unil.ch>
Description: modulr is an R implementation of the celebrated Module Pattern that allows you to encapsulate pieces of code into useful singleton units, namely modules that register their capabilities, export values and rely on other modules dependencies. modulr is widely inspired from RequireJS for Javascript, work of James Burke and other contributors from the Open Source Community.
Depends: gdata, pooh
Suggests: dplyr, magrittr, DBI, ROracle
License: MIT
Encoding: UTF-8
